\triangle MNP
\displaystyle \frac{8}{14}=\frac{4}{MP}\Rightarrow MP=7
\displaystyle \frac{14}{8}=\frac{7}{NP}\Rightarrow NP=4
\displaystyle\frac{14}{10}=\frac{7}{MN}\Rightarrow MN=5
=MP+NP+MN=7+4+5=16
